    "body": "### Topic\n\nSkip initial snapshot/full refresh\n\n### Relevant information\n\nHi Team,\nUsing **Airbyte OSS** with **Postgres Source v3.7.2** in **CDC mode**. For very large tables, the mandatory **initial snapshot** routinely exceeds the **24h initial load timeout** and retries restart from scratch, causing WAL bloat and repeated failures. I need a way to **start CDC directly from the current WAL LSN** (i.e., “new changes only”) after preloading history externally.\nThis matches prior requests/discussions:\n\n- Similar feature ask (skip snapshot / new changes only) was closed as not on the roadmap. [[github.com](https://github.com/airbytehq/airbyte/issues/20112)]\n- Initial load timeout (>24h) + non‑resumable retries block large tables. [[github.com](https://github.com/airbytehq/airbyte/issues/47448)]\n- Docs indicate CDC takes a snapshot first and CDC doesn’t support views, so view‑based workarounds don’t apply. [[docs.airbyte.com](https://docs.airbyte.com/integrations/sources/postgres/postgres-troubleshooting)]\n\n**Request:**\n\n1. A **CDC configuration to skip the initial snapshot** and begin from current LSN, or\n2. A **field to set a custom starting LSN** for the replication slot (after external backfill).\n3. (Nice‑to‑have) **Configurable initial load timeout** and/or **resume from last position** on failure.\n\nThis would let us onboard large tables (tens of millions+ rows) safely: bulk‑load history outside Airbyte, then let Airbyte CDC stream **only new changes.**\n\nThanks!\n\n---\n**Internal Tracking:** https://github.com/airbytehq/oncall/issues/11732",
