      "body": "Hi @avijayarajait, thank you for reporting this and for the thorough write-up!\n\nI understand the pain point — for very large tables, the mandatory initial snapshot in CDC mode can be a significant blocker, especially with the 24-hour initial load timeout causing retries that start from scratch and lead to WAL bloat.\n\nYour request is clear and well-reasoned:\n\n1. **Skip initial snapshot** and begin CDC from the current WAL LSN\n2. **Custom starting LSN** for the replication slot (after external backfill)\n3. **Configurable initial load timeout** and/or **resume from last position** on failure\n\nThis is a valid feature request — the underlying Debezium engine that powers Postgres CDC does support `snapshot.mode` options (e.g., `never`, `initial_only`, `when_needed`) that could enable this behavior, but the Airbyte Postgres source connector does not currently expose this configuration to users.\n\nI have escalated this to the internal team for evaluation. I will update this issue with a tracking link shortly.\n\n---\n**Need more help?** Join [Airbyte Community Slack](https://slack.airbyte.com) for peer support, or if you are a Cloud customer, [open a support ticket](https://support.airbyte.com) referencing this URL.\n\n<!--\nAirbyte uses AI to help us provide support to our community members.\n\nInternal reference link: https://app.devin.ai/sessions/f2e76730f71a4b91961593f0fd62eda4\n-->",
